						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-608375" title="">April 1, 2011</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">333</div>

				<p>I made this the other night when my boyfriend was coming from Canada (to the UK) and was extremely jet-lagged. As an English boy I had to teach him what biscuits were, but he absolutely LOVED them! And they really work so well with this delicious chilli! I froze some of the pre-formed biscuits as you suggested because I didn&#8217;t think we&#8217;d eat them all, and I had quite a bit of chilli leftover which I cooked up the following night with the biscuits and, interestingly, the biscuits were much larger and fluffier after being frozen! Don&#8217;t know whether anyone else has found this before but I thought it was quite interesting! I now made another batch and froze them for whenever I&#8217;m in a hurry (and hungry!!)</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
